WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Wataru?

00:00:07.960 --> 00:00:08.960
I...

00:00:09.270 --> 00:00:10.630
I should probably head home...

00:00:23.700 --> 00:00:25.010
- Let's go.
- Okay.

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:39.800
We're here.

00:00:40.130 --> 00:00:41.130
Huh?

00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:42.590
My place.

00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:47.610
Come on.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:54.570
Come on in.

00:00:55.960 --> 00:00:57.120
Excuse me.

00:00:57.430 --> 00:00:58.760
It's just a temporary place,

00:00:58.810 --> 00:01:00.379
but if you're willing to move in,

00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:01.660
I'm happy to find a better spot.

00:01:03.010 --> 00:01:04.510
You really don't give up, do you?

00:01:04.763 --> 00:01:06.083
I prefer the term "persistent."

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:12.060
What's wrong? Come inside.

00:01:17.130 --> 00:01:18.470
Aren't you staying for dinner?

00:01:21.010 --> 00:01:22.010
I am.

00:01:22.510 --> 00:01:23.510
Then get in here.

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:37.630
Welcome home.

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:43.230
Thanks for having me.

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:45.900
Yeah.

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:40.700
"Countdown To Yes"

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:52.800
(Episode 6)

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:05.290
Nice room.

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:12.800
Wait, I took this photo, didn't I?

00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:14.340
Yeah.

00:03:15.350 --> 00:03:17.240
Just how much do you love my work?

00:03:18.060 --> 00:03:19.130
A lot.

00:03:19.410 --> 00:03:20.410
Huh?

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:22.300
Looking at them brings it all back.

00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:24.640
The sound of the waves that day...

00:03:25.050 --> 00:03:26.310
and the smell of the fireworks.

00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:29.770
I really love your photos, Wataru.

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:33.810
Let's see who can keep their
sparkler going the longest.

00:03:34.010 --> 00:03:35.030
You're on.

00:03:36.460 --> 00:03:37.780
(September 26, 2017)
Is this good?

00:03:38.950 --> 00:03:39.950
Don't move.

00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:42.520
Okay, perfect.

00:03:42.870 --> 00:03:45.180
Go, go, go! Yes, yes, yes!

00:03:49.470 --> 00:03:50.470
There we go.

00:03:51.310 --> 00:03:53.750
Once I develop today's photos,
I'm going to hang them up too.

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:57.090
Can I have your roll of film, Minato?

00:03:57.410 --> 00:03:58.730
I'll take it back and develop it.

00:03:58.930 --> 00:04:00.290
He lets you use the darkroom?

00:04:01.080 --> 00:04:03.340
The manager said it's a perk of the job.

00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:05.160
Your manager is a saint...

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:06.420
Right?

00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:10.030
Today was so much fun.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:11.750
Go wash your hands.

00:04:12.230 --> 00:04:13.770
- Okay.
- Over here.

00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.590
Oh, you got a new shampoo.

00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:28.380
The one you bought
before was pricey, right?

00:04:28.580 --> 00:04:30.520
I like the kind that makes my hair soft.

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:36.940
So soft and smooth.

00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:39.340
Stop touching it, you'll get it wet.

00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:41.860
Is your face turning red?

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:43.410
It's just my allergies.

00:04:43.500 --> 00:04:44.840
Dry skin.

00:05:04.690 --> 00:05:05.960
I win!

00:05:06.250 --> 00:05:08.009
The longer you gargle, the better.

00:05:08.010 --> 00:05:10.570
No, the first one to finish wins!

00:05:24.630 --> 00:05:26.080
Oh, bean sprouts.

00:05:26.380 --> 00:05:27.930
Wataru, do you still burn them?

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:29.389
I do not burn them, thank you very much.

00:05:29.390 --> 00:05:30.449
You used to.

00:05:30.450 --> 00:05:31.730
How long ago was that?

00:05:32.570 --> 00:05:34.520
Back when we first moved in together.

00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:36.740
When we were 18.

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:42.500
(June 1, 2018)

00:05:52.430 --> 00:05:54.130
Liar, I know they're bitter.

00:05:57.200 --> 00:05:59.110
We're 26 now.

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:00.460
I'm still 25.

00:06:00.930 --> 00:06:02.130
You're younger than me.

00:06:02.170 --> 00:06:03.270
Show some respect.

00:06:10.930 --> 00:06:12.190
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

00:06:20.100 --> 00:06:21.580
This reminds me of my birthday.

00:06:22.610 --> 00:06:23.790
I know what you mean.

00:06:24.950 --> 00:06:26.470
(December 21, 2019)
- Cheers. - Cheers.

00:06:29.150 --> 00:06:31.070
We have to celebrate
our 10th year together too.

00:06:31.470 --> 00:06:33.400
The 10th year...

00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:34.840
25 years old?

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:36.900
Hey, will we still be together then?

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:39.660
Shut up, idiot.

00:06:40.030 --> 00:06:41.940
Slow down, you're drinking too fast.

00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:43.270
Want some water?

00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:44.470
Yeah.

00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:46.590
Even in our 10th year,

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:49.590
I'll still be by your side.

00:06:56.740 --> 00:06:57.740
Ten years.

00:06:58.320 --> 00:06:59.520
It went by in a flash.

00:07:00.190 --> 00:07:02.280
They say your 30s go by even faster.

00:07:02.970 --> 00:07:05.830
Ten years from now... we'll be 35.

00:07:06.940 --> 00:07:09.580
By then, we'll have known
each other for 20 years.

00:07:11.500 --> 00:07:13.580
We'll have spent over
half our lives together.

00:07:21.970 --> 00:07:23.820
But we had that three-year gap.

00:07:24.020 --> 00:07:25.020
Huh?

00:07:25.940 --> 00:07:28.170
The three years after graduation.

00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:30.380
That doesn't really
count as being "together."

00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:31.680
It counts.

00:07:31.840 --> 00:07:33.230
We didn't even see each other.

00:07:33.990 --> 00:07:35.550
When work got busy,

00:07:38.423 --> 00:07:39.833
I'd always talk to this guy.

00:07:40.100 --> 00:07:43.700
(March 20, 2022)

00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:45.090
The one I made?

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:47.950
What, were you lonely?

00:07:48.990 --> 00:07:50.190
I really love this thing.

00:07:54.440 --> 00:07:56.610
I'd pretend it was you
and tell it everything.

00:07:57.460 --> 00:07:58.880
So it wasn't really a gap.

00:07:59.940 --> 00:08:00.940
What?

00:08:01.980 --> 00:08:04.520
Thanks to him, I was able to
work hard on making good yogurt.

00:08:07.150 --> 00:08:09.790
Do you have any of your yogurt left?

00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:12.940
It's from the factory where I used to work.

00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:22.560
That's a lot of dairy.

00:08:23.240 --> 00:08:24.240
This one.

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:27.490
"Yogurt from the Land of
More Cows Than People."

00:08:28.360 --> 00:08:29.360
That's a great name.

00:08:29.760 --> 00:08:31.100
It's really good.

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:42.520
I want some too.

00:08:52.510 --> 00:08:53.510
Good, right?

00:08:57.230 --> 00:08:58.790
I hate to admit it, but it's delicious.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:00.000
Hate to admit it?

00:09:02.770 --> 00:09:04.230
It's because of this yogurt

00:09:04.430 --> 00:09:06.580
that you were stolen away to the north.

00:09:09.230 --> 00:09:10.230
You...

00:09:10.370 --> 00:09:12.250
You chose yogurt over photography.

00:09:12.710 --> 00:09:14.590
Why does it have to be one or the other?

00:09:14.800 --> 00:09:16.000
Because that's just how it is.

00:09:16.300 --> 00:09:17.500
Haven't you heard the saying?

00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:19.800
"If you chase two rabbits,
you'll catch neither."

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:21.000
Neither?

00:09:21.590 --> 00:09:24.380
If you want something,
you have to make a choice.

00:09:24.910 --> 00:09:26.300
And at that moment, Minato,

00:09:26.590 --> 00:09:27.990
you chose yogurt.

00:09:28.580 --> 00:09:29.580
Right?

00:09:29.980 --> 00:09:32.219
I wanted to make yogurt my career.

00:09:32.220 --> 00:09:32.770
See?

00:09:32.771 --> 00:09:34.280
But photography is important too.

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:36.870
I still take photos, and I still love it.

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:39.540
They're both important to me.

00:09:47.470 --> 00:09:48.749
Eating this much yogurt

00:09:48.750 --> 00:09:50.660
can't be good for you.

00:09:51.110 --> 00:09:52.660
Too much of anything is bad.

00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:53.830
That goes for everything.

00:09:54.640 --> 00:09:56.510
Maybe you should quit yogurt for a while.

00:09:57.330 --> 00:09:59.840
Quitting only makes me
crave it more. I've tested it.

00:10:00.590 --> 00:10:01.820
You tried?

00:10:02.370 --> 00:10:03.620
I'm not talking about yogurt.

00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:05.739
I'm talking about you.

00:10:05.740 --> 00:10:06.930
- Huh?
- Huh?

00:10:11.100 --> 00:10:14.090
I'm not even done with dinner,
and everything tastes like sugar.

00:10:14.310 --> 00:10:15.510
There's no added sugar in this.

00:10:15.530 --> 00:10:16.740
It's sweet enough for me.

00:10:17.330 --> 00:10:18.330
Huh.

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:26.560
Whoa, Minato, you're fast.

00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:31.040
Ready?

00:10:31.770 --> 00:10:33.780
- 9, 8, 7...
- 6.

00:10:34.090 --> 00:10:35.320
5! I win.

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:38.440
What? I lost again?

00:10:39.170 --> 00:10:42.430
I'm out of interesting stories to tell.

00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:46.240
Then tell me what you've been
up to for the past three years.

00:10:46.890 --> 00:10:47.890
What I've been doing?

00:10:48.830 --> 00:10:50.540
Just taking photos.

00:10:50.910 --> 00:10:52.620
Whether I was working or off the clock.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.320
I want to see.

00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:06.180
This was from Shioiri's wedding shoot.

00:11:08.710 --> 00:11:09.710
They look so happy.

00:11:16.450 --> 00:11:17.900
Oh, the manager...

00:11:21.880 --> 00:11:23.430
This is his son.

00:11:23.730 --> 00:11:24.950
I call him Big Bro.

00:11:25.150 --> 00:11:27.940
"Big Bro..."
Nice to meet you.

00:11:37.310 --> 00:11:39.510
The day I took my first client's photo...

00:11:40.850 --> 00:11:43.970
it finally felt like photography was
my job. I kept this as a memento.

00:11:44.690 --> 00:11:45.690
That's so cool.

00:11:46.210 --> 00:11:47.210
Right?

00:11:47.800 --> 00:11:50.130
You should just make a
living from photography too.

00:11:50.920 --> 00:11:52.990
What if we opened a studio together?

00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:54.670
That sounds nice.

00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:59.260
A huge studio right by the ocean.

00:12:24.870 --> 00:12:26.890
But then you disappeared.

00:12:28.390 --> 00:12:29.670
I won't disappear again.

00:12:30.260 --> 00:12:31.470
We'll see about that.

00:12:31.740 --> 00:12:33.110
Being apart made me realize...

00:12:34.290 --> 00:12:35.540
that being with you

00:12:36.080 --> 00:12:37.900
is when I'm truly happy.

00:12:41.500 --> 00:12:46.500
(September 4, 2015)

00:13:01.950 --> 00:13:03.390
Yokoi Minato.

00:13:03.620 --> 00:13:04.620
Yeah?

00:13:05.500 --> 00:13:06.500
What is it?

00:13:07.070 --> 00:13:08.570
You called my name.

00:13:10.720 --> 00:13:13.080
The first time you called me by my name...

00:13:14.400 --> 00:13:15.960
Wait, did you take this?

00:13:20.740 --> 00:13:23.030
I absolutely love your photos.

00:13:25.230 --> 00:13:28.010
Ever since you said you liked my work,

00:13:28.580 --> 00:13:29.780
I've been so happy.

00:13:32.030 --> 00:13:33.030
(September 16, 2015)
Whoa!

00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:36.120
Don't get it on me!

00:13:37.170 --> 00:13:38.170
Give me a sip.

00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:42.830
- Hey, I bought that! Why'd you drink first?
- My mom's gonna kill me.

00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:55.050
Want to see?

00:13:55.640 --> 00:13:56.640
I love them.

00:13:57.320 --> 00:13:59.510
I love your photos, Wataru.

00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:02.550
Man, I'm so happy.

00:14:03.910 --> 00:14:05.190
When I'm with you,

00:14:05.730 --> 00:14:07.870
I can actually feel my heart beating.

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:14.000
(August 6, 2019)

00:14:20.620 --> 00:14:21.790
You're so cute.

00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:42.680
I want to stay with you like this forever.

00:14:43.260 --> 00:14:44.340
That's what I was thinking.

00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:49.700
(March 19, 2022)

00:14:49.730 --> 00:14:51.030
It's freezing.

00:14:55.580 --> 00:14:57.460
It's still so cold.

00:15:07.080 --> 00:15:08.780
I couldn't believe

00:15:09.640 --> 00:15:10.940
I was actually leaving you.

00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:13.960
So...

00:15:14.240 --> 00:15:16.320
That's why I said you
were the one who left.

00:15:17.970 --> 00:15:20.170
When I decided to come back,

00:15:20.530 --> 00:15:22.460
all I wanted was to live with you again.

00:15:23.480 --> 00:15:24.480
Me too.

00:15:25.180 --> 00:15:27.296
When I'm with you,
I can't help but feel the same way.

00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:28.320
I'm so glad.

00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:31.440
I wish it could stay like this forever.

00:15:31.630 --> 00:15:33.050
- Then...
- We can live together.

00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:35.520
Just like back in college.

00:15:35.580 --> 00:15:37.370
Easy and fun.

00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:40.330
- That's not what I meant...
- Enough.

00:15:41.470 --> 00:15:44.150
Stop playing with semantics.

00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:46.550
I'm not. I'm serious.

00:15:47.380 --> 00:15:49.120
I don't get it.

00:15:49.700 --> 00:15:51.620
Why are you so obsessed
with being "boyfriends"?

00:15:51.950 --> 00:15:53.860
Why can't we just go back to how it was?

00:15:53.990 --> 00:15:55.270
We're best friends.

00:15:55.390 --> 00:15:56.690
Isn't that enough?

00:15:57.810 --> 00:15:58.980
I love you.

00:15:59.280 --> 00:16:00.480
And you love me.

00:16:01.310 --> 00:16:03.210
Being a couple wouldn't
be a problem at all.

00:16:03.710 --> 00:16:05.020
Nothing would have to change.

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:06.170
It would change.

00:16:06.171 --> 00:16:07.370
Like how? Tell me.

00:16:13.310 --> 00:16:14.040
Forget it.

00:16:14.041 --> 00:16:15.619
Actually, I'm over it.

00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:16.620
What?

00:16:16.720 --> 00:16:17.920
I don't love you anymore.

00:16:17.940 --> 00:16:19.390
I'm done with that.

00:16:22.810 --> 00:16:24.720
Being best friends is for the best.

00:16:25.630 --> 00:16:27.660
It's the happiest we can be.

00:16:28.920 --> 00:16:30.749
What we have right now...

00:16:30.750 --> 00:16:31.950
is perfect.

00:16:32.120 --> 00:16:33.470
This is enough.

00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:36.510
How do you know it couldn't be better?

00:16:37.190 --> 00:16:38.790
We haven't even tried.

00:16:51.160 --> 00:16:52.570
Okay, I win.

00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:53.730
Wataru.

00:16:53.850 --> 00:16:55.510
Shower. I'm going to take a shower.

00:16:55.780 --> 00:16:56.780
I'm tired.

00:17:13.490 --> 00:17:14.630
What is even going on...

00:17:14.990 --> 00:17:15.990
What was that?

00:17:18.710 --> 00:17:19.840
Minato...

00:17:20.110 --> 00:17:21.390
He's acting different.

00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:27.190
He doesn't smell like he usually does.

00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:30.790
Get it together.

00:17:31.220 --> 00:17:32.250
Minato is a friend...

00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:33.610
Minato is a friend...

00:17:33.870 --> 00:17:34.990
Minato is just a friend.

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:37.970
I don't love him.

00:17:46.710 --> 00:17:47.820
There's only one bed.

00:17:48.390 --> 00:17:50.140
Dammit, I didn't think this through.

00:17:51.080 --> 00:17:52.080
What's up?

00:17:52.080 --> 00:17:53.080
That was a fast shower.

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:54.730
I'm always fast.

00:17:56.670 --> 00:17:58.210
Oh, the pillow...

00:17:58.660 --> 00:18:00.070
I meant to go buy one.

00:18:01.580 --> 00:18:02.810
I'll sleep on the floor.

00:18:03.180 --> 00:18:04.180
Why?

00:18:04.460 --> 00:18:05.680
It's too cramped for two.

00:18:05.740 --> 00:18:06.906
I don't even have a spare blanket.

00:18:06.930 --> 00:18:08.650
- It's fine, really...
- No, it's not.

00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:10.130
I'll sleep on the floor.

00:18:10.180 --> 00:18:11.060
You take the bed.

00:18:11.061 --> 00:18:12.490
No, no, no, absolutely not.

00:18:12.850 --> 00:18:14.970
The host sleeping on
the floor? That's weird.

00:18:20.410 --> 00:18:21.410
Are you...

00:18:21.910 --> 00:18:22.910
mad at me?

00:18:26.740 --> 00:18:28.840
You smell like my house.

00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:47.830
- Does that mean I win?
- Not a chance.

00:19:07.510 --> 00:19:08.510
What's that?

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:09.880
Toner.

00:19:10.140 --> 00:19:11.376
Since when do you use that stuff?

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:12.890
When I was in Hokkaido,

00:19:13.130 --> 00:19:15.420
my face got all dry and cracked like yours.

00:19:15.800 --> 00:19:16.800
It hurt so much.

00:19:24.670 --> 00:19:25.670
Does it sting?

00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:27.040
No...

00:19:27.190 --> 00:19:28.290
You just startled me.

00:19:29.090 --> 00:19:30.090
Once you use this,

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:32.180
your face won't hurt even in winter.

00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:35.500
I highly recommend it for your dry skin.

00:19:37.540 --> 00:19:38.540
Oh.

00:19:38.810 --> 00:19:39.980
So bouncy.

00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:42.220
It'll be even better
once I put on the lotion.

00:19:52.430 --> 00:19:53.530
Surprised?

00:19:55.070 --> 00:19:56.170
It's soaking in...

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:57.300
Wait, really?

00:19:57.350 --> 00:19:58.350
Sorry.

00:20:00.270 --> 00:20:01.870
It's you... you've soaked into my heart.

00:20:03.510 --> 00:20:04.510
What?

00:20:04.690 --> 00:20:05.690
What does that even mean?

00:20:07.020 --> 00:20:08.220
Back then...

00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:11.510
I didn't actually want to leave.

00:20:14.910 --> 00:20:16.460
Before I moved out of the apartment,

00:20:17.060 --> 00:20:18.290
on that last night,

00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:20.570
we slept on the floor together, remember?

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:22.680
Oh, yeah.

00:20:23.090 --> 00:20:24.190
I remember that.

00:20:24.410 --> 00:20:25.510
It was freezing.

00:20:26.070 --> 00:20:28.330
Because you packed all the blankets away.

00:20:30.360 --> 00:20:32.000
You could've just done it in the morning.

00:20:33.190 --> 00:20:35.040
You didn't stop me, so it's your fault too.

00:20:39.860 --> 00:20:43.090
That was the first time I couldn't sleep.

00:20:47.030 --> 00:20:48.240
And that's when

00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:52.660
I realized I loved you.

00:20:56.900 --> 00:20:59.340
I thought I'd eventually
forget once we were apart.

00:21:00.970 --> 00:21:02.070
But I didn't.

00:21:14.150 --> 00:21:15.150
Me too...

00:21:19.410 --> 00:21:22.490
I couldn't sleep that night either.

00:21:25.680 --> 00:21:26.890
Because you were leaving.

00:21:27.280 --> 00:21:28.380
I hated it.

00:21:39.340 --> 00:21:41.550
Can we do what we couldn't do back then?

00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:47.440
I told you, I'm over it.

00:21:49.940 --> 00:21:52.450
Can I kiss you?

00:22:13.070 --> 00:22:14.070
You can...

00:22:48.163 --> 00:22:49.963
I wish morning would never come.

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:01.000
(Next Episode)

00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:02.000
Wataru...

00:23:03.690 --> 00:23:06.230
Minato and I...

00:23:06.560 --> 00:23:08.040
Are you two moving in together again?

00:23:08.480 --> 00:23:10.279
Why are you deciding things on your own?

00:23:10.280 --> 00:23:12.100
I don't want to. It's not a good idea.

00:23:12.430 --> 00:23:14.300
Then why did you say I could kiss you?